      <text >
         <body>
            <div type="recto" n="19691001_0007">
               <figure>
                  <graphic url="19691001_0007r.png"/>
                  <figDesc>A reproduction of David's painting of Bonaparte crossing the
                     Alps</figDesc>
                  <head>Couleurs et lumière de France. Bonaparte franchissant les Alpes par David.
                     (Musée de Versailles).</head>
               </figure>
            </div>
            <div type="verso" facs="19691001_0007v.png">
               <div type="message">
                  <p>Wed.</p>
                  <p>Many thanks for letter. Yes have the book, (and liked it) have read it. And
                     will send it to you plus letter immediately on getting back i.e Monday., </p>
                  <p>You must go to Versailles, Louis, it's got lots &amp; lots &amp; lots of
                     CONKERS</p>
                  <salute>– Love Kath.</salute>
               </div>
               <div type="destination">
                  <p><stamp>Paris Gare Montparnasse <date when="1969-10-01T16:30">16h30 1-10-1969</date></stamp>
                     <stamp type="postage">République - La Marianne de Cheffer. Face value 30c. Mauve (Yvert &amp;
                        Tellier N°1536)</stamp>
                     <address>    <addrLine>Louis Burnard</addrLine>
               <addrLine>4, Freeland Cottages,</addrLine><addrLine>
               Church Lane</addrLine><addrLine>
               Stanton St. John</addrLine><addrLine>
               OXFORD</addrLine><addrLine>
               ANGLETERRE</addrLine></address></p>
               </div>
            </div>
         </body>
      </text>
